data.chText: 严厉的；苛刻的；要求别人服从的
data.enText: serious and often disapproving; expecting sb to obey you

data.chText: 严厉的面容 / 表情 / 目光
警方正制订更严厉的措施打击犯罪活动。
data.enText: The police are planning sterner measures to combat crime.

data.chText: 性格十分坚强；有很大的毅力
data.enText: to have a stronger character and to be more determined in dealing with problems than other people
the back end of a ship or boat
all the way from the front of a ship to the back

data.chText: 性格十分坚强；有很大的毅力
data.enText: to have a stronger character and to be more determined in dealing with problems than other people
all the way from the front of a ship to the back

tr: the rear part of a ship
the fleshy part of the human body that you sit on
example: he deserves a good kick in the butt
are you going to sit on your fanny and do nothing?

tr: severe and unremitting in making demands
of a stern or strict bearing or demeanor
not to be placated or appeased or moved by entreaty
example: Russia's final hour, it seemed, approached with inexorable certainty

value.def: Stern words or actions are very severe.

example.ex: Mr Straw issued a stern warning to those who persist in violence...
example.tran: 斯特劳先生向那些坚持进行暴力活动的人发出了严正警告。

example.ex: He said stern measures would be taken against the killers...
Michael gave the dog a stern look.
example.tran: 迈克尔狠狠瞪了那只狗一眼。

example.ex: 'We will take the necessary steps,' she said sternly.
example.tran: “我们将采取必要措施，”她厉声说道。

value.def: Someone who is stern is very serious and strict.

example.ex: Her father was stern and hard to please.
example.tran: 她父亲很苛刻，让他满意很难。

value.def: The stern of a boat is the back part of it.
value.tran: 船尾;艉部 from stem to stern

value.def: If you say that someone is made of sterner stuff, you mean that they have a strong personality and are capable of overcoming difficulties and problems.

example.ex: Whoever this woman is, she's made of sterner stuff than I am.
example.tran: 不管这个女人是谁，她都比我坚强。
